This paper is primarily focused on security protocol analysis, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also introduces a framework for reasoning about security properties using dynamic spatial logic specifications, which falls under the category of logic in computer science (cs.LO). The paper also discusses the computational model used, which is a variant of existing pi-calculi, falling under the category of programming languages (cs.PL). The paper also mentions the use of a model-checking algorithm, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses how the results may be used to reason about security properties of open systems, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE).
